Love this app , checking the consistency by LED providers on claimed wavelengths. I miss a way to measure par values , hope this will be incorporated in future releases. I am using a Samsung S9 Update-Jan16"21 Thanks so much for adding par , amazing , changed my rating to 5* I'll put out the word to the reefing community.

Works as described; intuitive interface and great for quick analysis. Would appreciate some way to get a more precise frequency reading, x-axis scale is hard to interpolate. Maybe numerical peak value(s) or numerical value at finger touch point on active graph? Or perhaps custom min/max for x-axis value display?

Works great on the One Plus 7 Pro. Pretty easy to figure out, app does what it says and the measures appear to be fairly consistent. Question for devs: is it possible to add a feature that provides the numerical data behind the "light color spectrum"? Maybe something than can be exported as a .CSV file? That would be really helpful.
Does not work black screen

Does what it says, and gives consistent measurements. Can't say anything about accuracy though, as I don't have any other meters to compare it to. There are a few UI/UX issues- can't back out of screenshots; can't delete screenshots; menu is hardly intuitive (maybe is more understandable for pros? Idk.); would not measure on first run; photo metadata is movable, but if you leave it at the bottom of the screen, you can't see it in the screenshots; seems to limit how many screenshots you get.

Is there a way to disable the sounds? I could not find any setting for that. I hear a click on every press of a button, even if the phone is set on mute. Also, sometimes the app stops computing in realtime and freezes all the numerical values, even though the scenery is changing. A restart is therefore required. Otherwise it's a pretty good app.
It works for our analysis of led color, need to be updated with apple version to get more stars
